{"article_id":"Bjpv6XRx5ExrIzx7","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Boston Marathon bombing investigation took a dramatic turn overnight","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"as two suspects","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"sought by federal authorities","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"fought local police in a violent exchange of bullets and explosions .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"By early Friday one of the suspects and a Massachusetts Institute of Technology campus police officer were dead ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"another police officer was wounded ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and the remaining suspect had fled into nearby Watertown , Mass .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"The area is under lockdown","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"as police conduct a house-to-house search for a man","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"presumed to carry firearms and bombs .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Authorities shut down Boston public transit","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"and warned residents of a huge swath of close-in suburbs","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"to hunker down .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Officials said","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"the suspect at large is the second of two","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"identified on Thursday in video and photo stills","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"released to the public","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"- known since as suspect No . 1 and suspect No . 2 .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"In those images , he was wearing a white hat","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"turned backwards","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"and a gray hooded sweatshirt .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"According to the Associated Press ,","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"the suspects are brothers from an area of Russia near Chechnya .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"The AP said","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"sources have identified the suspect","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"who remains at large","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"as Dzhokhar A. Tsarnaev , 19 , of Cambridge , Mass .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"\" We believe this to be a terrorist , \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Boston Police Commissioner Ed Davis said .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"\" We believe this to be a man","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"who came here","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"to kill people . \"","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"The exact sequence of events remained unclear Friday morning","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"as news accounts of the suspects ' actions differed .","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"About 10:30 p.m. Thursday , police received a report of a robbery at a convenience store in Kendall Square , a Cambridge neighborhood near the MIT campus .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Shortly afterward , authorities discovered an MIT police officer shot dead at Main and Vassar Streets ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"according to The Boston Globe .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"Authorities on Friday morning had not yet determined the exact relationship of these events .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"According to a statement from the Middlesex District Attorney ' s Office and Cambridge police ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"the MIT officer had been responding to reports of a \" disturbance . \"","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"NBC News reported","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"that the two suspects car-jacked the MIT officer ' s cruiser .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Other accounts said","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"the police officer was discovered in his car .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Shortly afterward , the two suspects car-jacked a Mercedes sport utility vehicle at gunpoint ,","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"briefly imprisoning the driver in the car .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"The driver was subsequently able to escape at a gas station along Memorial Drive , a major area thoroughfare","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"that connects Cambridge with suburbs to the west .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"The two suspects drove off along Memorial Drive toward Watertown , with a train of law enforcement vehicles in pursuit ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"according to the Globe .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Authorities exchanged gunfire with the suspects during the chase .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"In the exchange , a transit officer was wounded ,","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"according to police .","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"The suspects apparently were then cornered in an area of Watertown","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"and exited their hijacked SUV","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"to continue the firefight .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Citing eyewitnesses ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"The New York Times depicted a wild scene","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"in which two slightly built young men traded volleys of gunfire with approaching police .","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"One of the men had a device","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"that resembled a pressure cooker ,","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"one witness told the Times .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"Pressure cookers were used in the bombs","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"left Monday along the Marathon route ,","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"according to the FBI .","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"In the Watertown battle , the suspect \" lit \" the pressure cooker","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"and tossed it toward police ,","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"said the Times .","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"But it went only 20 yards or so","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"and did not endanger officers","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"when it exploded ,","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"according to this account .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"Eventually one of the two men ran toward police officers .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"He was tackled or shot .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"The remaining suspect got back into the SUV ,","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"turned it toward a police cordon ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"and blasted through at full throttle .","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"Doctors at Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center in Boston said","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"they had treated a man with multiple gunshot wounds and explosive trauma early Friday morning .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"The man died .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Hospital officials were unable to confirm","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"whether the deceased was the FBI 's suspect No . 1 .","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"However , law enforcement officials announced at an early-morning press conference","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"that a suspect was dead .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"They said","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"the two men","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"who had fought with police","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"were the same two men","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"depicted in the photos","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"released to the public on Thursday .","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"The man still at large on Friday morning ,","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"they said ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"is suspect No . 2 .","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"Surveillance video depicts him","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"placing a bag in the area of the second Boston Marathon bomb .","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"\" There is a terrorist on the loose , \"","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"said one police officer at the impromptu press conference .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"NBC News ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"citing law enforcement sources ,","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"the two men in question have \" international links \"","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"and have been in the United States legally for about a year .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":103,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":105,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":106,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":107,"text":"Police warned residents from Cambridge out to Newton to stay indoors","depth":4},{"id":108,"text":"and not to answer their doors except for an identified police officer .","depth":4},{"id":109,"text":"They told businesses to keep closed .","depth":4},{"id":110,"text":"Boston schools were closed , as well as all Boston-area public transit ,","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"including subways , trains , and buses .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"\" People at bus or subway stations , we are asking them to go home , \"","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"said Kurt Schwartz , head of the Massachusetts state Homeland Security Department , at a 6 a.m. press conference .","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"\" We do not want people congregating","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"and waiting for the system to come back on . \"","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":231,"left":217,"right":230,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":217,"left":147,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":128,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":122,"right":127,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":119,"right":121,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":0,"right":118,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":117,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":4,"right":120,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":120,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":124,"right":126,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":7,"right":123,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":10,"right":125,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":135,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":13,"right":134,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},